post_text:
We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

post_text:
Dear AJB families:

We have now been given approval to serve meals to you beginning TOMORROW March 26th. This will be a “grab and go” process for AJB stakeholders AND THE ENTIRE COMMUNITY AROUND AJB. For ANYONE that is 18 years old or younger. Please pull up to the main doors and we will bring your food to you between the hours of 9am to 2pm.

We will also provide enough meals for the weekend on Fridays as well. The meal program will be available over our spring break as well.

We care and we will get through this together!

Stay healthy and safe,

Principal Hill

December 12, 2019 at 4:40 PM ·

Today the RISE team toured Andrew J. Brown Academy with Representative Robin Shackleford and City-County Councillor La Keisha Jackson. In conversations with students, parents, and staff members, we learned about this school’s incredible sense of community and their commitment to ensuring that all of their scholars reach their highest potential. Many thanks to Principal James Hill, Andrew J. Brown staff, and to our elected officials for their persistent leadership in this community.
